{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/14099", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/14099/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/14099/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/14099/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/14099", "id": 381613938, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzODE2MTM5Mzg=", "number": 14099, "title": "Transposed Convolution output shape does not take into account dilation", "user": {"login": "Coolnesss", "id": 4622983, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQ2MjI5ODM=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/4622983?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss", "html_url": "https://github.com/Coolnesss", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Coolnesss/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": {"login": "soumith", "id": 1310570, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzMTA1NzA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1310570?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith", "html_url": "https://github.com/soumith", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "assignees": [{"login": "soumith", "id": 1310570, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzMTA1NzA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/1310570?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith", "html_url": "https://github.com/soumith", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/soumith/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2018-11-16T14:08:31Z", "updated_at": "2018-11-19T18:36:02Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "body_html": "<h2><g-emoji class=\"g-emoji\" alias=\"books\" fallback-src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4da.png\">\ud83d\udcda</g-emoji> Documentation</h2>\n<p>Hey, there seems to be a simple mistake in the equation for the output of all the transposed convolution layers (e.g <a href=\"https://pytorch.org/docs/master/nn.html#convtranspose2d\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://pytorch.org/docs/master/nn.html#convtranspose2d</a>). The equations do not take into account dilation.</p>\n<p>I believe the correct formula should be (in the 1d case)</p>\n<pre><code>(L_in - 1) * s - 2 * p + (k - 1)*d + o_p + 1\n</code></pre>\n<p>where <code>L_in, s, p, k, d, o_p</code> are input length, stride, padding, kernel size, dilation and output padding, respectively.</p>", "body_text": "\ud83d\udcda Documentation\nHey, there seems to be a simple mistake in the equation for the output of all the transposed convolution layers (e.g https://pytorch.org/docs/master/nn.html#convtranspose2d). The equations do not take into account dilation.\nI believe the correct formula should be (in the 1d case)\n(L_in - 1) * s - 2 * p + (k - 1)*d + o_p + 1\n\nwhere L_in, s, p, k, d, o_p are input length, stride, padding, kernel size, dilation and output padding, respectively.", "body": "## \ud83d\udcda Documentation\r\n\r\nHey, there seems to be a simple mistake in the equation for the output of all the transposed convolution layers (e.g https://pytorch.org/docs/master/nn.html#convtranspose2d). The equations do not take into account dilation. \r\n\r\nI believe the correct formula should be (in the 1d case)\r\n\r\n```\r\n(L_in - 1) * s - 2 * p + (k - 1)*d + o_p + 1\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhere `L_in, s, p, k, d, o_p` are input length, stride, padding, kernel size, dilation and output padding, respectively."}